&lt;p&gt;This Solicitation/Request for Quote is changed to a &lt;strong style=&quot;mso-bidi-font-weight: normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;100% Set Aside for Small Business&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The U.S. Vegetable Laboratory will solicit quotations from&amp;nbsp;Small Businesses to obtain elevator maintenance service on one ThyssenKrupp-Dover elevator which was installed in 2003 at the U.S. Vegetable Laboratory, 2700 Savannah Highway, Charleston, SC 29414.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The contractor shall provide all manpower, materials, tools, supplies, equipment, transportation, supervision, incidental engineering and management necessary to perform the inspection, testing, elevator communication monitoring services, maintenance, repair and component replacement as required to maintain the elevator system in accordance with manufactures original specification.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NAICS code for this requirement is 238290, and the small business size standard is $14M.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The Government intends to issue a firm fixed price service contract, a base year plus four option years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;RFQ was&amp;nbsp;issued on or after Nov. 8, 2013.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;All contractors must be registered in the System for Award Management &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.sam.gov&quot;&gt;http://www.sam.gov&lt;/a&gt; database prior to any contract award.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The solicitation will be distributed solely through the General Services Administration&apos;s Federal Business Opportunities web site &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.fedbizopps.gov/&quot;&gt;http://www.fedbizopps.gov/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Hard copies of the solicitation document will not be available.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The site provides downloading instructions.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;All future information about this acquisition, including amendments, will also be distributed solely through this site.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Interested parties are responsible for monitoring this site to ensure that they have the most up-to-date information.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Contractors are reminded that they are responsible for obtaining and acknowledging all amendments to this solicitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

THIS IS A SOURCES SOUGHT NOTICE FOR INFORMATION AND PLANNING PURPOSES ONLY. The 505th Command and Control Wing (505 CCW) is requesting information and conducting market research to determine if there are potential sources which have the capability to provide security services at the 505 CCW and its subordinate units. This announcement closes 4:00 p.m. CST on Monday, 6 Jan 2014. The Government is seeking industry input from all sources (small and large businesses) at this time. Small Business concerns are highly encouraged to respond to this request in order for the Government to determine if this acquisition should be a total small business set aside under the auspices of the Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) Part 19. The anticipated North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) for this requirement is 561621 (Alarm System Monitoring Services) with a corresponding size standard of $19M. Interested parties must be registered under NAICS 561621 in SAM (System for Award Management) at www.sam.gov, formerly known as CCR (Central Contractor Registration). The Government plans to consider all information submitted in response to this Sources Sought Notice.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;p&gt;FAR 52.215-3: (a) The Government does not intend to award a contract on the basis of this RFI or to otherwise pay for the information solicited except as an allowable cost under other contracts as provided in subsection 31.205-18, bid and proposal costs, of the Federal Acquisition Regulation. (b) Although &quot;proposal&quot; and &quot;offeror&quot; are used in this RFI, your response will be treated as information only. It shall not be used as a proposal. (c) This RFI is for planning and market research purposes only and should not be considered as a request for proposals or as a solicitation to do business with the Government.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Air Combat Command, Acquisition Management Integration Center (ACC AMIC) PKBC-OL (505 CCW/PK), Hurlburt Field, FL, is in the process of determining the acquisition strategy to obtain non-personal services to support Wing and subordinate units to ensure the protection and safeguarding of Collateral, Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI), Special Technical Operations (STO) and Special Access Programs (SAP) activities in the following core security mission areas: Security Management, Personnel Security, Information Security, Physical Security, Information Systems Security/Information Assurance (IA), Communications Security (COMSEC), Security Awareness, Training and Education (SATE), Operation Security (OPSEC), Industrial Security, Foreign Disclosure, SAP Systems Administration, and security courseware development and academic instruction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Performance will consist of a Phase-In/Transition period (length of Phase-In period is TBD), one (1) base period, and four (4) one-year option periods. The Government anticipates making award on or about 30 Jun 2014, with the Phase-In/Transition period covering 26 Aug - 25 Sep 2014, and the actual contract performance to start 26 Sep 2014. The Request For Proposal (RFP) release date is to be determined. Please note: This is an estimated posting timeframe and it is the responsibility of the interested parties to monitor the Federal Business Opportunity website at www.fbo.gov for all subsequent postings. A draft Performance Work Statement (PWS) is posted in conjunction with this notice to provide the size, scope, and complexity of this requirement. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The predecessor Security Support contract was not a small business set aside. The Government is seeking industry input to determine if there are adequate small business concerns that are capable of performing the follow-on requirement. A determination regarding the set aside status for this effort has not been made.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is not a formal Request for Proposal (RFP), and no contract will result from this notice, nor does it commit the Government to any acquisition for these services. All interested parties should submit a capabilities package (please limit to no more than 25 pages total) outlining your company&apos;s key business abilities relevant to the performance of this requirement and addressing the questions found in Attachment 1. Please submit the requested information to Capt Brooke Cultra at brooke.cultra@hurlburt.af.mil and Mr. Eric Lingad at eric.lingad@hurlburt.af.mil NLT 4:00 p.m. CST, Monday, 6 Jan 2014.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;Specific items and quantities to be procured are as follows:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;p&gt;JC021A-OM&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;qty (8)&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;HP Tipping Point maintenance SW; Maintenance renewal for HPS2500N IPS 3GSPS-S_GT/1-10GE/2-GBFBR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;JC200A-OM&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;qty (3) HP Tipping Point maintenance SW; Maintenance renewal for HP SMS Appliance 2/25-IPS Systems License&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
